{
  "text": "In the international pooled analysis, adjustment for current smoking eliminated an apparent protective effect of alcohol drinking. [CITATION_1] Rossing et al, however, reported a decreased risk of papillary thyroid cancer in women associated with alcohol consumption after controlling for smoking. [CITATION_2] In the present study, we found the significant effects of drinking after adjustment for smoking, and of smoking after adjustment for drinking. However, the findings Smoking, Drinking, and Thyroid Cancer Risk",
